cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing and annotation schemes for morphosyntactic details of language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves mapping and interoperability between different annotation projects, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of corpora and validation techniques could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the critical evaluation of the two annotation projects could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
